-- Morin Joins PSP and Canadian Imperial Hires Lauze, Vlaad Says
-- B y   K a t i a   D m i t r i e v a
-- 2013-11-15T21:33:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-15/morin-joins-psp-and-canadian-imperial-hires-lauze-vlaad-says.html
  Canaccord Genuity Group Inc. (CF)  hired
Kevin Wright as a technology associate analyst from Macquarie
Group Ltd., according to Vlaad & Co., a Toronto-based financial
services recruiting firm.  Other moves noted in the “Bill’s Buzz” weekly  newsletter 
include:  * David Morin joined Public Sector Pension Investment Board in
the private equity group from Credit Suisse Group Ag in  London 
where he was an associate.  * Massimo Voci was hired as a research analyst at Mackie
Research Capital Corp. Lawrence Rhee also joined Mackie as an
 investment banking  managing director. Both were formerly at  MGI
Securities Inc.  * Investment banking analyst David Bonasia joined Bastion
Infrastructure Group from Canaccord.  * Canadian Imperial Bank of Commerce hired Benoit Lauze to head
ECM origination; investment bankers Michael Cochrane and Ryan
Voegeli as co-heads of diversified industries, technology, media
and telecommunications; Jason Stefanson as vice chair of
investment banking; and named Jean Raymond head of Montreal
investment banking in addition to his responsibilities as head
of Quebec wholesale banking.  * The Bank of  New York  Mellon Corp. hired Paul Kamin from CIBC
as a vice president and eastern Canadian business development
officer.  * Cameron Davies left The Kirchner Group to join Rare Earth
Salts as president and chief operating officer.  * Beacon Securities Ltd. added analyst Kuno Ryckborst, who was
previously with PI Financial Corp.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Katia Dmitrieva in Toronto at 
 edmitrieva1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Scanlan at 
 dscanlan@bloomberg.net  